3. Bastarnas: for their location, see map. They are the first Germanic people to appear in history, Philip III. of Macedon having. in 179 nc.. induced them to aid him in his war against the Romans ; but he died before anything could 116 accomplished. Under their leader, Clondicus. they offered to furnish 20,000 men to his successor, Perseus, but the latter alienated them by his parsimony. Their cus- toms and manners were accurately described by Polybius, the chief source of later writers.
